President Uhuru Kenyatta&rsquo;s Jubilee Party has won the support of 183 former civic leaders from Kitui county, who have endorsed his re-election. Wiper enjoys massive support in the county.The former councillors held a meeting in a Kitui hotel last week and resolved to popularise Uhuru in the entire county.The secret strategy meeting in the home county of NASA&rsquo;s Kalonzo Musyoka was hosted by the Kitui assembly minority leader Alex Nganga.Sources said participants knew it would be hard to sell Uhuru and Jubilee on Kalonzo&rsquo;s home turf. However, the former councillors said they will do their best to earn the President a sizeable number of votes. Kitui County Former Councillors&rsquo; Forum chairman Gideon Munyalo said they will be Uhuru&rsquo;s foot soldiers.